You don't lose your insurance just because you lose your job.  You
lose your insurance because you failed to plan for inevitable job
loss.  You failed to realize that YOU, not your employer, would be
responsible for YOUR health between jobs.

You don't discontinue your household fire insurance between jobs.  You
don't discontinue your car insurance between jobs.  You don't
discontinue food purchases between jobs.  You don't turn off the water
between jobs.

Why do you not make plans to insure your health between jobs?  You
don't save for this inevitablity for the same reason you don't save
for your retirement.  You don't save for these inevitablilties because
you would rather buy a bunch of techno-toys  (ON CREDIT).

As I said a few days ago, there are two kinds of people: Those who pay
interest and those who earn interest.

Unfortunately a squirrel has more economic sense than most Americans.
